5300 
5301 void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitRecord(const RecordType *RT,
5302  CharUnits offset) {
5303  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
5304 
5305  // If this is a union, remember that we had one, because it might mess
5306  // up the ordering of layout entries.
5307  if (RD->isUnion())
5308  IsDisordered = true;
5309 
5310  const ASTRecordLayout *recLayout = nullptr;
5311  visitAggregate(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end(), offset,
5312  [&](const FieldDecl *field) -> CharUnits {
5313  if (!recLayout)
5314  recLayout = &CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
5315  auto offsetInBits = recLayout->getFieldOffset(field->getFieldIndex());
5316  return CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(offsetInBits);
5317  });
5318 }
5319 
5320 template <class Iterator, class GetOffsetFn>
5321 void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitAggregate(Iterator begin, Iterator end,
5322  CharUnits aggregateOffset,
5323  const GetOffsetFn &getOffset) {
5324  for (; begin != end; ++begin) {
5325  auto field = *begin;
5326 
5327  // Skip over bitfields.
5328  if (field->isBitField()) {
5329  continue;
5330  }
5331 
5332  // Compute the offset of the field within the aggregate.
5333  CharUnits fieldOffset = aggregateOffset + getOffset(field);
5334 
5335  visitField(field, fieldOffset);
5336  }
5337 }
5338 
5339 /// Collect layout information for the given fields into IvarsInfo.
5340 void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitField(const FieldDecl *field,
5341  CharUnits fieldOffset) {
5342  QualType fieldType = field->getType();
5343 
5344  // Drill down into arrays.
5345  uint64_t numElts = 1;
5346  if (auto arrayType = CGM.getContext().getAsIncompleteArrayType(fieldType)) {
5347  numElts = 0;
5348  fieldType = arrayType->getElementType();
5349  }
5350  // Unlike incomplete arrays, constant arrays can be nested.
5351  while (auto arrayType = CGM.getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(fieldType)) {
5352  numElts *= arrayType->getSize().getZExtValue();
5353  fieldType = arrayType->getElementType();
5354  }
5355 
5356  assert(!fieldType->isArrayType() && "ivar of non-constant array type?");
5357 
5358  // If we ended up with a zero-sized array, we've done what we can do within
5359  // the limits of this layout encoding.
5360  if (numElts == 0) return;
5361 
5362  // Recurse if the base element type is a record type.
5363  if (auto recType = fieldType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5364  size_t oldEnd = IvarsInfo.size();
5365 
5366  visitRecord(recType, fieldOffset);
5367 
5368  // If we have an array, replicate the first entry's layout information.
5369  auto numEltEntries = IvarsInfo.size() - oldEnd;
5370  if (numElts != 1 && numEltEntries != 0) {
5371  CharUnits eltSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(recType);
5372  for (uint64_t eltIndex = 1; eltIndex != numElts; ++eltIndex) {
5373  // Copy the last numEltEntries onto the end of the array, adjusting
5374  // each for the element size.
5375  for (size_t i = 0; i != numEltEntries; ++i) {
5376  auto firstEntry = IvarsInfo[oldEnd + i];
5377  IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(firstEntry.Offset + eltIndex * eltSize,
5378  firstEntry.SizeInWords));
5379  }
5380  }
5381  }
5382 
5383  return;
5384  }
5385 
5386  // Classify the element type.
5387  Qualifiers::GC GCAttr = GetGCAttrTypeForType(CGM.getContext(), fieldType);
5388 
5389  // If it matches what we're looking for, add an entry.
5390  if ((ForStrongLayout && GCAttr == Qualifiers::Strong)
5391  || (!ForStrongLayout && GCAttr == Qualifiers::Weak)) {
5392  assert(CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(fieldType)
5393  == CGM.getPointerSize());
5394  IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(fieldOffset, numElts));
5395  }
5396 }
5397 
5398 /// buildBitmap - This routine does the horsework of taking the offsets of
5399 /// strong/weak references and creating a bitmap. The bitmap is also
5400 /// returned in the given buffer, suitable for being passed to \c dump().
5401 llvm::Constant *IvarLayoutBuilder::buildBitmap(CGObjCCommonMac &CGObjC,
5402  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<unsigned char> &buffer) {
5403  // The bitmap is a series of skip/scan instructions, aligned to word
5404  // boundaries. The skip is performed first.
5405  const unsigned char MaxNibble = 0xF;
5406  const unsigned char SkipMask = 0xF0, SkipShift = 4;
5407  const unsigned char ScanMask = 0x0F, ScanShift = 0;
5408 
5409  assert(!IvarsInfo.empty() && "generating bitmap for no data");
5410 
5411  // Sort the ivar info on byte position in case we encounterred a
5412  // union nested in the ivar list.
5413  if (IsDisordered) {
5414  // This isn't a stable sort, but our algorithm should handle it fine.
5415  llvm::array_pod_sort(IvarsInfo.begin(), IvarsInfo.end());
5416  } else {
5417  assert(llvm::is_sorted(IvarsInfo));
5418  }
5419  assert(IvarsInfo.back().Offset < InstanceEnd);
5420 
5421  assert(buffer.empty());
5422 
5423  // Skip the next N words.
5424  auto skip = [&](unsigned numWords) {
5425  assert(numWords > 0);
5426 
5427  // Try to merge into the previous byte. Since scans happen second, we
5428  // can't do this if it includes a scan.
5429  if (!buffer.empty() && !(buffer.back() & ScanMask)) {
5430  unsigned lastSkip = buffer.back() >> SkipShift;
5431  if (lastSkip < MaxNibble) {
5432  unsigned claimed = std::min(MaxNibble - lastSkip, numWords);
5433  numWords -= claimed;
5434  lastSkip += claimed;
5435  buffer.back() = (lastSkip << SkipShift);
5436  }
5437  }
5438 
5439  while (numWords >= MaxNibble) {
5440  buffer.push_back(MaxNibble << SkipShift);
5441  numWords -= MaxNibble;
5442  }
5443  if (numWords) {
5444  buffer.push_back(numWords << SkipShift);
5445  }
5446  };
5447 
5448  // Scan the next N words.
5449  auto scan = [&](unsigned numWords) {
5450  assert(numWords > 0);
5451 
5452  // Try to merge into the previous byte. Since scans happen second, we can
5453  // do this even if it includes a skip.
5454  if (!buffer.empty()) {
5455  unsigned lastScan = (buffer.back() & ScanMask) >> ScanShift;
5456  if (lastScan < MaxNibble) {
5457  unsigned claimed = std::min(MaxNibble - lastScan, numWords);
5458  numWords -= claimed;
5459  lastScan += claimed;
5460  buffer.back() = (buffer.back() & SkipMask) | (lastScan << ScanShift);
5461  }
5462  }
5463 
5464  while (numWords >= MaxNibble) {
5465  buffer.push_back(MaxNibble << ScanShift);
5466  numWords -= MaxNibble;
5467  }
5468  if (numWords) {
5469  buffer.push_back(numWords << ScanShift);
5470  }
5471  };
5472 
5473  // One past the end of the last scan.
5474  unsigned endOfLastScanInWords = 0;
5475  const CharUnits WordSize = CGM.getPointerSize();
5476 
5477  // Consider all the scan requests.
5478  for (auto &request : IvarsInfo) {
5479  CharUnits beginOfScan = request.Offset - InstanceBegin;
5480 
5481  // Ignore scan requests that don't start at an even multiple of the
5482  // word size. We can't encode them.
5483  if ((beginOfScan % WordSize) != 0) continue;
5484 
5485  // Ignore scan requests that start before the instance start.
5486  // This assumes that scans never span that boundary. The boundary
5487  // isn't the true start of the ivars, because in the fragile-ARC case
5488  // it's rounded up to word alignment, but the test above should leave
5489  // us ignoring that possibility.
5490  if (beginOfScan.isNegative()) {
5491  assert(request.Offset + request.SizeInWords * WordSize <= InstanceBegin);
5492  continue;
5493  }
5494 
5495  unsigned beginOfScanInWords = beginOfScan / WordSize;
5496  unsigned endOfScanInWords = beginOfScanInWords + request.SizeInWords;
5497 
5498  // If the scan starts some number of words after the last one ended,
5499  // skip forward.
5500  if (beginOfScanInWords > endOfLastScanInWords) {
5501  skip(beginOfScanInWords - endOfLastScanInWords);
5502 
5503  // Otherwise, start scanning where the last left off.
5504  } else {
5505  beginOfScanInWords = endOfLastScanInWords;
5506 
5507  // If that leaves us with nothing to scan, ignore this request.
5508  if (beginOfScanInWords >= endOfScanInWords) continue;
5509  }
5510 
5511  // Scan to the end of the request.
5512  assert(beginOfScanInWords < endOfScanInWords);
5513  scan(endOfScanInWords - beginOfScanInWords);
5514  endOfLastScanInWords = endOfScanInWords;
5515  }
5516 
5517  if (buffer.empty())
5518  return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
5519 
5520  // For GC layouts, emit a skip to the end of the allocation so that we
5521  // have precise information about the entire thing. This isn't useful
5522  // or necessary for the ARC-style layout strings.
5523  if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
5524  unsigned lastOffsetInWords =
5525  (InstanceEnd - InstanceBegin + WordSize - CharUnits::One()) / WordSize;
5526  if (lastOffsetInWords > endOfLastScanInWords) {
5527  skip(lastOffsetInWords - endOfLastScanInWords);
5528  }
5529  }
5530 
5531  // Null terminate the string.
5532  buffer.push_back(0);
5533 
5534  auto *Entry = CGObjC.CreateCStringLiteral(
5535  reinterpret_cast<char *>(buffer.data()), ObjCLabelType::ClassName);
5536  return getConstantGEP(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Entry, 0, 0);
5537 }
5538 
5539 /// BuildIvarLayout - Builds ivar layout bitmap for the class
5540 /// implementation for the __strong or __weak case.
5541 /// The layout map displays which words in ivar list must be skipped
5542 /// and which must be scanned by GC (see below). String is built of bytes.
5543 /// Each byte is divided up in two nibbles (4-bit each). Left nibble is count
5544 /// of words to skip and right nibble is count of words to scan. So, each
5545 /// nibble represents up to 15 workds to skip or scan. Skipping the rest is
5546 /// represented by a 0x00 byte which also ends the string.
5547 /// 1. when ForStrongLayout is true, following ivars are scanned:
5548 /// - id, Class
5549 /// - object *
5550 /// - __strong anything
5551 ///
5552 /// 2. When ForStrongLayout is false, following ivars are scanned:
5553 /// - __weak anything
5554 ///
5555 llvm::Constant *
5556 CGObjCCommonMac::BuildIvarLayout(const ObjCImplementationDecl *OMD,
5557  CharUnits beginOffset, CharUnits endOffset,
5558  bool ForStrongLayout, bool HasMRCWeakIvars) {
5559  // If this is MRC, and we're either building a strong layout or there
5560  // are no weak ivars, bail out early.
5561  llvm::Type *PtrTy = CGM.Int8PtrTy;
5562  if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC &&
5563  !CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
5564  (ForStrongLayout || !HasMRCWeakIvars))
5565  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrTy);
5566 
5567  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI = OMD->getClassInterface();
5568  SmallVector<const ObjCIvarDecl*, 32> ivars;
5569 
5570  // GC layout strings include the complete object layout, possibly
5571  // inaccurately in the non-fragile ABI; the runtime knows how to fix this
5572  // up.
5573  //
5574  // ARC layout strings only include the class's ivars. In non-fragile
5575  // runtimes, that means starting at InstanceStart, rounded up to word
5576  // alignment. In fragile runtimes, there's no InstanceStart, so it means
5577  // starting at the offset of the first ivar, rounded up to word alignment.
5578  //
5579  // MRC weak layout strings follow the ARC style.
5580  CharUnits baseOffset;
5581  if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC) {
5582  for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = OI->all_declared_ivar_begin();
5583  IVD; IVD = IVD->getNextIvar())
5584  ivars.push_back(IVD);
5585 
5586  if (isNonFragileABI()) {
5587  baseOffset = beginOffset; // InstanceStart
5588  } else if (!ivars.empty()) {
5589  baseOffset =
5590  CharUnits::fromQuantity(ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, OMD, ivars[0]));
5591  } else {
5592  baseOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
5593  }
5594 
5595  baseOffset = baseOffset.alignTo(CGM.getPointerAlign());
5596  }
5597  else {
5598  CGM.getContext().DeepCollectObjCIvars(OI, true, ivars);
5599 
5600  baseOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
5601  }
5602 
5603  if (ivars.empty())
5604  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrTy);
5605 
5606  IvarLayoutBuilder builder(CGM, baseOffset, endOffset, ForStrongLayout);
5607 
5608  builder.visitAggregate(ivars.begin(), ivars.end(), CharUnits::Zero(),
5609  [&](const ObjCIvarDecl *ivar) -> CharUnits {
5610  return CharUnits::fromQuantity(ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, OMD, ivar));
5611  });
5612 
5613  if (!builder.hasBitmapData())
5614  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrTy);
5615 
5616  llvm::SmallVector<unsigned char, 4> buffer;
5617  llvm::Constant *C = builder.buildBitmap(*this, buffer);
5618 
5619  if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCGCBitmapPrint && !buffer.empty()) {
5620  printf("\n%s ivar layout for class '%s': ",
5621  ForStrongLayout ? "strong" : "weak",
5622  OMD->getClassInterface()->getName().str().c_str());
5623  builder.dump(buffer);
5624  }
5625  return C;
5626 }

5640 
5641 llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::GetMethodVarType(const FieldDecl *Field) {
5642  std::string TypeStr;
5643  CGM.getContext().getObjCEncodingForType(Field->getType(), TypeStr, Field);
5644 
5645  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = MethodVarTypes[TypeStr];
5646  if (!Entry)
5647  Entry = CreateCStringLiteral(TypeStr, ObjCLabelType::MethodVarType);
5648  return getConstantGEP(VMContext, Entry, 0, 0);
5649 }
5650 
5651 llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::GetMethodVarType(const ObjCMethodDecl *D,
5652  bool Extended) {
5653  std::string TypeStr =
5654  CGM.getContext().getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(D, Extended);
5655 
5656  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = MethodVarTypes[TypeStr];
5657  if (!Entry)
5658  Entry = CreateCStringLiteral(TypeStr, ObjCLabelType::MethodVarType);
5659  return getConstantGEP(VMContext, Entry, 0, 0);
5660 }
5661 
5662 // FIXME: Merge into a single cstring creation function.
5663 llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::GetPropertyName(IdentifierInfo *Ident) {
5664  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = PropertyNames[Ident];
5665  if (!Entry)
5666  Entry = CreateCStringLiteral(Ident->getName(), ObjCLabelType::PropertyName);
5667  return getConstantGEP(VMContext, Entry, 0, 0);
5668 }
5669 
5670 // FIXME: Merge into a single cstring creation function.
5671 // FIXME: This Decl should be more precise.
5672 llvm::Constant *
5673 CGObjCCommonMac::GetPropertyTypeString(const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
5674  const Decl *Container) {
5675  std::string TypeStr =
5676  CGM.getContext().getObjCEncodingForPropertyDecl(PD, Container);
5677  return GetPropertyName(&CGM.getContext().Idents.get(TypeStr));
5678 }
5679 
5680 void CGObjCMac::FinishModule() {
5681  EmitModuleInfo();
5682 
5683  // Emit the dummy bodies for any protocols which were referenced but
5684  // never defined.
5685  for (auto &entry : Protocols) {
5686  llvm::GlobalVariable *global = entry.second;
5687  if (global->hasInitializer())
5688  continue;
5689 
5690  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
5691  auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ProtocolTy);
5692  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolExtensionPtrTy);
5693  values.add(GetClassName(entry.first->getName()));
5694  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListPtrTy);
5695  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionListPtrTy);
5696  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionListPtrTy);
5697  values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(global);
5698  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(global);
5699  }
5700 
5701  // Add assembler directives to add lazy undefined symbol references
5702  // for classes which are referenced but not defined. This is
5703  // important for correct linker interaction.
5704  //
5705  // FIXME: It would be nice if we had an LLVM construct for this.
5706  if ((!LazySymbols.empty() || !DefinedSymbols.empty()) &&
5707  CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO()) {
5708  SmallString<256> Asm;
5709  Asm += CGM.getModule().getModuleInlineAsm();
5710  if (!Asm.empty() && Asm.back() != '\n')
5711  Asm += '\n';
5712 
5713  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Asm);
5714  for (const auto *Sym : DefinedSymbols)
5715  OS << "\t.objc_class_name_" << Sym->getName() << "=0\n"
5716  << "\t.globl .objc_class_name_" << Sym->getName() << "\n";
5717  for (const auto *Sym : LazySymbols)
5718  OS << "\t.lazy_reference .objc_class_name_" << Sym->getName() << "\n";
5719  for (const auto &Category : DefinedCategoryNames)
5720  OS << "\t.objc_category_name_" << Category << "=0\n"
5721  << "\t.globl .objc_category_name_" << Category << "\n";
5722 
5723  CGM.getModule().setModuleInlineAsm(OS.str());
5724  }
5725 }

5728  : CGObjCCommonMac(cgm), ObjCTypes(cgm), ObjCEmptyCacheVar(nullptr),
5729  ObjCEmptyVtableVar(nullptr) {
5730  ObjCABI = 2;
5731 }

5734 
5735 ObjCCommonTypesHelper::ObjCCommonTypesHelper(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &cgm)
5736  : VMContext(cgm.getLLVMContext()), CGM(cgm), ExternalProtocolPtrTy(nullptr)
5737 {
5738  CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
5739  ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
5740 
5741  ShortTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Types.ConvertType(Ctx.ShortTy));
5742  IntTy = CGM.IntTy;
5743  LongTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Types.ConvertType(Ctx.LongTy));
5744  Int8PtrTy = CGM.Int8PtrTy;
5745  Int8PtrPtrTy = CGM.Int8PtrPtrTy;
5746 
5747  // arm64 targets use "int" ivar offset variables. All others,
5748  // including OS X x86_64 and Windows x86_64, use "long" ivar offsets.
5749  if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64)
5750  IvarOffsetVarTy = IntTy;
5751  else
5752  IvarOffsetVarTy = LongTy;
5753 
5754  ObjectPtrTy =
5755  cast<llvm::PointerType>(Types.ConvertType(Ctx.getObjCIdType()));
5756  PtrObjectPtrTy =
5757  llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ObjectPtrTy);
5758  SelectorPtrTy =
5759  cast<llvm::PointerType>(Types.ConvertType(Ctx.getObjCSelType()));
5760 
5761  // I'm not sure I like this. The implicit coordination is a bit
5762  // gross. We should solve this in a reasonable fashion because this
5763  // is a pretty common task (match some runtime data structure with
5764  // an LLVM data structure).
5765 
5766  // FIXME: This is leaked.
5767  // FIXME: Merge with rewriter code?
5768 
5769  // struct _objc_super {
5770  // id self;
5771  // Class cls;
5772  // }
5773  RecordDecl *RD = RecordDecl::Create(Ctx, TTK_Struct,
5774  Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
5775  SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
5776  &Ctx.Idents.get("_objc_super"));
5777  RD->addDecl(FieldDecl::Create(Ctx, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
5778  nullptr, Ctx.getObjCIdType(), nullptr, nullptr,
5779  false, ICIS_NoInit));
5780  RD->addDecl(FieldDecl::Create(Ctx, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
5781  nullptr, Ctx.getObjCClassType(), nullptr,
5782  nullptr, false, ICIS_NoInit));
5783  RD->completeDefinition();
5784 
5785  SuperCTy = Ctx.getTagDeclType(RD);
5786  SuperPtrCTy = Ctx.getPointerType(SuperCTy);
5787 
5788  SuperTy = cast<llvm::StructType>(Types.ConvertType(SuperCTy));
5789  SuperPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(SuperTy);
5790 
5791  // struct _prop_t {
5792  // char *name;
5793  // char *attributes;
5794  // }
5795  PropertyTy = llvm::StructType::create("struct._prop_t", Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy);
5796 
5797  // struct _prop_list_t {
5798  // uint32_t entsize; // sizeof(struct _prop_t)
5799  // uint32_t count_of_properties;
5800  // struct _prop_t prop_list[count_of_properties];
5801  // }
5802  PropertyListTy = llvm::StructType::create(
5803  "struct._prop_list_t", IntTy, IntTy, llvm::ArrayType::get(PropertyTy, 0));
5804  // struct _prop_list_t *
5805  PropertyListPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(PropertyListTy);
5806 
5807  // struct _objc_method {
5808  // SEL _cmd;
5809  // char *method_type;
5810  // char *_imp;
5811  // }
5812  MethodTy = llvm::StructType::create("struct._objc_method", SelectorPtrTy,
5813  Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy);
5814 
5815  // struct _objc_cache *
5816  CacheTy = llvm::StructType::create(VMContext, "struct._objc_cache");
5817  CachePtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(CacheTy);
5818 }

6104  // const struct _method_list_t * const class_methods;

6107  // const struct _prop_list_t * const class_properties;
6108  // const uint32_t size;
6109  // }

6112  MethodListnfABIPtrTy, ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy, PropertyListPtrTy,
6113  PropertyListPtrTy, IntTy);

6116  CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
6117  ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
6118

6120  // struct _message_ref_t {
6121  // IMP messenger;
6122  // SEL name;
6123  // };

6129  &Ctx.Idents.get("_message_ref_t"));

6131  nullptr, Ctx.VoidPtrTy, nullptr, nullptr, false,
6132  ICIS_NoInit));
6133  RD->addDecl(FieldDecl::Create(Ctx, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
6134  nullptr, Ctx.getObjCSelType(), nullptr, nullptr,
6135  false, ICIS_NoInit));

6139  MessageRefCPtrTy = Ctx.getPointerType(MessageRefCTy);
6140  MessageRefTy = cast<llvm::StructType>(Types.ConvertType(MessageRefCTy));
6141

6161  // };

6173 
6174 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::AddModuleClassList(
6175  ArrayRef<llvm::GlobalValue *> Container, StringRef SymbolName,
6176  StringRef SectionName) {
6177  unsigned NumClasses = Container.size();
6178 
6179  if (!NumClasses)
6180  return;
6181 
6182  SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 8> Symbols(NumClasses);
6183  for (unsigned i=0; i<NumClasses; i++)
6184  Symbols[i] = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Container[i],
6185  ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6186  llvm::Constant *Init =
6187  llvm::ConstantArray::get(llvm::ArrayType::get(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy,
6188  Symbols.size()),
6189  Symbols);
6190 
6191  // Section name is obtained by calling GetSectionName, which returns
6192  // sections in the __DATA segment on MachO.
6193  assert((!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO() ||
6194  SectionName.startswith("__DATA")) &&
6195  "SectionName expected to start with __DATA on MachO");
6196  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
6197  CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), false,
6198  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Init, SymbolName);
6199  GV->setAlignment(
6200  llvm::Align(CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(Init->getType())));
6201  GV->setSection(SectionName);
6202  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
6203 }
6204 
6205 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::FinishNonFragileABIModule() {
6206  // nonfragile abi has no module definition.
6207 
6208  // Build list of all implemented class addresses in array
6209  // L_OBJC_LABEL_CLASS_$.
6210 
6211  for (unsigned i=0, NumClasses=ImplementedClasses.size(); i<NumClasses; i++) {
6212  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = ImplementedClasses[i];
6213  assert(ID);
6214  if (ObjCImplementationDecl *IMP = ID->getImplementation())
6215  // We are implementing a weak imported interface. Give it external linkage
6216  if (ID->isWeakImported() && !IMP->isWeakImported()) {
6217  DefinedClasses[i]->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage);
6218  DefinedMetaClasses[i]->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage);
6219  }
6220  }
6221 
6222  AddModuleClassList(DefinedClasses, "OBJC_LABEL_CLASS_$",
6223  GetSectionName("__objc_classlist",
6224  "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6225 
6226  AddModuleClassList(DefinedNonLazyClasses, "OBJC_LABEL_NONLAZY_CLASS_$",
6227  GetSectionName("__objc_nlclslist",
6228  "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6229 
6230  // Build list of all implemented category addresses in array
6231  // L_OBJC_LABEL_CATEGORY_$.
6232  AddModuleClassList(DefinedCategories, "OBJC_LABEL_CATEGORY_$",
6233  GetSectionName("__objc_catlist",
6234  "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6235  AddModuleClassList(DefinedStubCategories, "OBJC_LABEL_STUB_CATEGORY_$",
6236  GetSectionName("__objc_catlist2",
6237  "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6238  AddModuleClassList(DefinedNonLazyCategories, "OBJC_LABEL_NONLAZY_CATEGORY_$",
6239  GetSectionName("__objc_nlcatlist",
6240  "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6241 
6242  EmitImageInfo();
6243 }
6244 
6245 /// isVTableDispatchedSelector - Returns true if SEL is not in the list of
6246 /// VTableDispatchMethods; false otherwise. What this means is that
6247 /// except for the 19 selectors in the list, we generate 32bit-style
6248 /// message dispatch call for all the rest.
6249 bool CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::isVTableDispatchedSelector(Selector Sel) {
6250  // At various points we've experimented with using vtable-based
6251  // dispatch for all methods.
6252  switch (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getObjCDispatchMethod()) {
6253  case CodeGenOptions::Legacy:
6254  return false;
6255  case CodeGenOptions::NonLegacy:
6256  return true;
6257  case CodeGenOptions::Mixed:
6258  break;
6259  }
6260 
6261  // If so, see whether this selector is in the white-list of things which must
6262  // use the new dispatch convention. We lazily build a dense set for this.
6263  if (VTableDispatchMethods.empty()) {
6264  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("alloc"));
6265  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("class"));
6266  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("self"));
6267  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("isFlipped"));
6268  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("length"));
6269  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("count"));
6270 
6271  // These are vtable-based if GC is disabled.
6272  // Optimistically use vtable dispatch for hybrid compiles.
6273  if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::GCOnly) {
6274  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("retain"));
6275  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("release"));
6276  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("autorelease"));
6277  }
6278 
6279  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("allocWithZone"));
6280  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("isKindOfClass"));
6281  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("respondsToSelector"));
6282  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("objectForKey"));
6283  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("objectAtIndex"));
6284  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("isEqualToString"));
6285  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("isEqual"));
6286 
6287  // These are vtable-based if GC is enabled.
6288  // Optimistically use vtable dispatch for hybrid compiles.
6289  if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
6290  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("hash"));
6291  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("addObject"));
6292 
6293  // "countByEnumeratingWithState:objects:count"
6294  IdentifierInfo *KeyIdents[] = {
6295  &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("countByEnumeratingWithState"),
6296  &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("objects"),
6297  &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("count")
6298  };
6299  VTableDispatchMethods.insert(
6300  CGM.getContext().Selectors.getSelector(3, KeyIdents));
6301  }
6302  }
6303 
6304  return VTableDispatchMethods.count(Sel);
6305 }
6306 
6307 /// BuildClassRoTInitializer - generate meta-data for:
6308 /// struct _class_ro_t {
6309 /// uint32_t const flags;
6310 /// uint32_t const instanceStart;
6311 /// uint32_t const instanceSize;
6312 /// uint32_t const reserved; // only when building for 64bit targets
6313 /// const uint8_t * const ivarLayout;
6314 /// const char *const name;
6315 /// const struct _method_list_t * const baseMethods;
6316 /// const struct _protocol_list_t *const baseProtocols;
6317 /// const struct _ivar_list_t *const ivars;
6318 /// const uint8_t * const weakIvarLayout;
6319 /// const struct _prop_list_t * const properties;
6320 /// }
6321 ///
6322 llvm::GlobalVariable * CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::BuildClassRoTInitializer(
6323  unsigned flags,
6324  unsigned InstanceStart,
6325  unsigned InstanceSize,
6326  const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
6327  std::string ClassName = std::string(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString());
6328 
6329  CharUnits beginInstance = CharUnits::fromQuantity(InstanceStart);
6330  CharUnits endInstance = CharUnits::fromQuantity(InstanceSize);
6331 
6332  bool hasMRCWeak = false;
6333  if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
6334  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_CompiledByARC;
6335  else if ((hasMRCWeak = hasMRCWeakIvars(CGM, ID)))
6336  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasMRCWeakIvars;
6337 
6338  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6339  auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassRonfABITy);
6340 
6341  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, flags);
6342  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, InstanceStart);
6343  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, InstanceSize);
6344  values.add((flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta)
6345  ? GetIvarLayoutName(nullptr, ObjCTypes)
6346  : BuildStrongIvarLayout(ID, beginInstance, endInstance));
6347  values.add(GetClassName(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
6348 
6349  // const struct _method_list_t * const baseMethods;
6350  SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> methods;
6351  if (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta) {
6352  for (const auto *MD : ID->class_methods())
6353  if (!MD->isDirectMethod())
6354  methods.push_back(MD);
6355  } else {
6356  for (const auto *MD : ID->instance_methods())
6357  if (!MD->isDirectMethod())
6358  methods.push_back(MD);
6359  }
6360 
6361  values.add(emitMethodList(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6362  (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta)
6363  ? MethodListType::ClassMethods
6364  : MethodListType::InstanceMethods,
6365  methods));
6366 
6367  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = ID->getClassInterface();
6368  assert(OID && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::BuildClassRoTInitializer");
6369  values.add(EmitProtocolList("_OBJC_CLASS_PROTOCOLS_$_"
6370  + OID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6371  OID->all_referenced_protocol_begin(),
6372  OID->all_referenced_protocol_end()));
6373 
6374  if (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta) {
6375  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.IvarListnfABIPtrTy);
6376  values.add(GetIvarLayoutName(nullptr, ObjCTypes));
6377  values.add(EmitPropertyList(
6378  "_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6379  ID, ID->getClassInterface(), ObjCTypes, true));
6380  } else {
6381  values.add(EmitIvarList(ID));
6382  values.add(BuildWeakIvarLayout(ID, beginInstance, endInstance, hasMRCWeak));
6383  values.add(EmitPropertyList(
6384  "_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6385  ID, ID->getClassInterface(), ObjCTypes, false));
6386  }
6387 
6388  llvm::SmallString<64> roLabel;
6389  llvm::raw_svector_ostream(roLabel)
6390  << ((flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta) ? "_OBJC_METACLASS_RO_$_"
6391  : "_OBJC_CLASS_RO_$_")
6392  << ClassName;
6393 
6394  return finishAndCreateGlobal(values, roLabel, CGM);
6395 }
6396 
6397 /// Build the metaclass object for a class.
6398 ///
6399 /// struct _class_t {
6400 /// struct _class_t *isa;
6401 /// struct _class_t * const superclass;
6402 /// void *cache;
6403 /// IMP *vtable;
6404 /// struct class_ro_t *ro;
6405 /// }
6406 ///
6407 llvm::GlobalVariable *
6408 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::BuildClassObject(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *CI,
6409  bool isMetaclass,
6410  llvm::Constant *IsAGV,
6411  llvm::Constant *SuperClassGV,
6412  llvm::Constant *ClassRoGV,
6413  bool HiddenVisibility) {
6414  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6415  auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy);
6416  values.add(IsAGV);
6417  if (SuperClassGV) {
6418  values.add(SuperClassGV);
6419  } else {
6420  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy);
6421  }
6422  values.add(ObjCEmptyCacheVar);
6423  values.add(ObjCEmptyVtableVar);
6424  values.add(ClassRoGV);
6425 
6426  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
6427  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GetClassGlobal(CI, isMetaclass, ForDefinition));
6428  values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(GV);
6429 
6430  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6431  GV->setSection("__DATA, __objc_data");
6432  GV->setAlignment(llvm::Align(
6433  CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy)));
6434  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6435  if (HiddenVisibility)
6436  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6437  return GV;
6438 }
6439 
6440 bool CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::ImplementationIsNonLazy(
6441  const ObjCImplDecl *OD) const {
6442  return OD->getClassMethod(GetNullarySelector("load")) != nullptr ||
6443  OD->getClassInterface()->hasAttr<ObjCNonLazyClassAttr>() ||
6444  OD->hasAttr<ObjCNonLazyClassAttr>();
6445 }
6446 
6447 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassSizeInfo(const ObjCImplementationDecl *OID,
6448  uint32_t &InstanceStart,
6449  uint32_t &InstanceSize) {
6450  const ASTRecordLayout &RL =
6451  CGM.getContext().getASTObjCImplementationLayout(OID);
6452 
6453  // InstanceSize is really instance end.
6454  InstanceSize = RL.getDataSize().getQuantity();
6455 
6456  // If there are no fields, the start is the same as the end.
6457  if (!RL.getFieldCount())
6458  InstanceStart = InstanceSize;
6459  else
6460  InstanceStart = RL.getFieldOffset(0) / CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
6461 }
6462 
6463 static llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes getStorage(CodeGenModule &CGM,
6464  StringRef Name) {
6465  IdentifierInfo &II = CGM.getContext().Idents.get(Name);
6466  TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
6467  DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
6468 
6469  const VarDecl *VD = nullptr;
6470  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&II))
6471  if ((VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Result)))
6472  break;
6473 
6474  if (!VD)
6475  return llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass;
6476  if (VD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
6477  return llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass;
6478  if (VD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6479  return llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass;
6480  return llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass;
6481 }
6482 
6483 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateClass(const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
6484  if (!ObjCEmptyCacheVar) {
6485  ObjCEmptyCacheVar =
6486  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.CacheTy, false,
6487  llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
6488  "_objc_empty_cache");
6489  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6490  ObjCEmptyCacheVar->setDLLStorageClass(getStorage(CGM, "_objc_empty_cache"));
6491 
6492  // Only OS X with deployment version <10.9 use the empty vtable symbol
6493  const llvm::Triple &Triple = CGM.getTarget().getTriple();
6494  if (Triple.isMacOSX() && Triple.isMacOSXVersionLT(10, 9))
6495  ObjCEmptyVtableVar =
6496  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ImpnfABITy, false,
6497  llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
6498  "_objc_empty_vtable");
6499  else
6500  ObjCEmptyVtableVar =
6501  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ObjCTypes.ImpnfABITy->getPointerTo());
6502  }
6503 
6504  // FIXME: Is this correct (that meta class size is never computed)?
6505  uint32_t InstanceStart =
6506  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy);
6507  uint32_t InstanceSize = InstanceStart;
6508  uint32_t flags = NonFragileABI_Class_Meta;
6509 
6510  llvm::Constant *SuperClassGV, *IsAGV;
6511 
6512  const auto *CI = ID->getClassInterface();
6513  assert(CI && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateClass - class is 0");
6514 
6515  // Build the flags for the metaclass.
6516  bool classIsHidden = (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6517  ? !CI->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()
6518  : CI->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility;
6519  if (classIsHidden)
6520  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Hidden;
6521 
6522  // FIXME: why is this flag set on the metaclass?
6523  // ObjC metaclasses have no fields and don't really get constructed.
6524  if (ID->hasNonZeroConstructors() || ID->hasDestructors()) {
6525  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors;
6526  if (!ID->hasNonZeroConstructors())
6527  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXDestructorOnly;
6528  }
6529 
6530  if (!CI->getSuperClass()) {
6531  // class is root
6532  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Root;
6533 
6534  SuperClassGV = GetClassGlobal(CI, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition);
6535  IsAGV = GetClassGlobal(CI, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
6536  } else {
6537  // Has a root. Current class is not a root.
6538  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Root = ID->getClassInterface();
6539  while (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = Root->getSuperClass())
6540  Root = Super;
6541 
6542  const auto *Super = CI->getSuperClass();
6543  IsAGV = GetClassGlobal(Root, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
6544  SuperClassGV = GetClassGlobal(Super, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
6545  }
6546 
6547  llvm::GlobalVariable *CLASS_RO_GV =
6548  BuildClassRoTInitializer(flags, InstanceStart, InstanceSize, ID);
6549 
6550  llvm::GlobalVariable *MetaTClass =
6551  BuildClassObject(CI, /*metaclass*/ true,
6552  IsAGV, SuperClassGV, CLASS_RO_GV, classIsHidden);
6553  CGM.setGVProperties(MetaTClass, CI);
6554  DefinedMetaClasses.push_back(MetaTClass);
6555 
6556  // Metadata for the class
6557  flags = 0;
6558  if (classIsHidden)
6559  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Hidden;
6560 
6561  if (ID->hasNonZeroConstructors() || ID->hasDestructors()) {
6562  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors;
6563 
6564  // Set a flag to enable a runtime optimization when a class has
6565  // fields that require destruction but which don't require
6566  // anything except zero-initialization during construction. This
6567  // is most notably true of __strong and __weak types, but you can
6568  // also imagine there being C++ types with non-trivial default
6569  // constructors that merely set all fields to null.
6570  if (!ID->hasNonZeroConstructors())
6571  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXDestructorOnly;
6572  }
6573 
6574  if (hasObjCExceptionAttribute(CGM.getContext(), CI))
6575  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Exception;
6576 
6577  if (!CI->getSuperClass()) {
6578  flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Root;
6579  SuperClassGV = nullptr;
6580  } else {
6581  // Has a root. Current class is not a root.
6582  const auto *Super = CI->getSuperClass();
6583  SuperClassGV = GetClassGlobal(Super, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition);
6584  }
6585 
6586  GetClassSizeInfo(ID, InstanceStart, InstanceSize);
6587  CLASS_RO_GV =
6588  BuildClassRoTInitializer(flags, InstanceStart, InstanceSize, ID);
6589 
6590  llvm::GlobalVariable *ClassMD =
6591  BuildClassObject(CI, /*metaclass*/ false,
6592  MetaTClass, SuperClassGV, CLASS_RO_GV, classIsHidden);
6593  CGM.setGVProperties(ClassMD, CI);
6594  DefinedClasses.push_back(ClassMD);
6595  ImplementedClasses.push_back(CI);
6596 
6597  // Determine if this class is also "non-lazy".
6598  if (ImplementationIsNonLazy(ID))
6599  DefinedNonLazyClasses.push_back(ClassMD);
6600 
6601  // Force the definition of the EHType if necessary.
6602  if (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Exception)
6603  (void) GetInterfaceEHType(CI, ForDefinition);
6604  // Make sure method definition entries are all clear for next implementation.
6605  MethodDefinitions.clear();
6606 }
6607 
6608 /// GenerateProtocolRef - This routine is called to generate code for
6609 /// a protocol reference expression; as in:
6610 /// @code
6611 /// @protocol(Proto1);
6612 /// @endcode
6613 /// It generates a weak reference to l_OBJC_PROTOCOL_REFERENCE_$_Proto1
6614 /// which will hold address of the protocol meta-data.
6615 ///
6616 llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateProtocolRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6617  const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
6618 
6619  // This routine is called for @protocol only. So, we must build definition
6620  // of protocol's meta-data (not a reference to it!)
6621  assert(!PD->isNonRuntimeProtocol() &&
6622  "attempting to get a protocol ref to a static protocol.");
6623  llvm::Constant *Init =
6624  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GetOrEmitProtocol(PD),
6625  ObjCTypes.getExternalProtocolPtrTy());
6626 
6627  std::string ProtocolName("_OBJC_PROTOCOL_REFERENCE_$_");
6628  ProtocolName += PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6629 
6630  CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
6631 
6632  llvm::GlobalVariable *PTGV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(ProtocolName);
6633  if (PTGV)
6634  return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PTGV->getValueType(), PTGV, Align);
6635  PTGV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), false,
6636  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, Init,
6637  ProtocolName);
6638  PTGV->setSection(GetSectionName("__objc_protorefs",
6639  "coalesced,no_dead_strip"));
6640  PTGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6641  PTGV->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
6642  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6643  PTGV->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ProtocolName));
6644  CGM.addUsedGlobal(PTGV);
6645  return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PTGV->getValueType(), PTGV, Align);
6646 }
6647 
6648 /// GenerateCategory - Build metadata for a category implementation.
6649 /// struct _category_t {
6650 /// const char * const name;
6651 /// struct _class_t *const cls;
6652 /// const struct _method_list_t * const instance_methods;
6653 /// const struct _method_list_t * const class_methods;
6654 /// const struct _protocol_list_t * const protocols;
6655 /// const struct _prop_list_t * const properties;
6656 /// const struct _prop_list_t * const class_properties;
6657 /// const uint32_t size;
6658 /// }
6659 ///
6660 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateCategory(const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *OCD) {
6661  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface = OCD->getClassInterface();
6662  const char *Prefix = "_OBJC_$_CATEGORY_";
6663 
6664  llvm::SmallString<64> ExtCatName(Prefix);
6665  ExtCatName += Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6666  ExtCatName += "_$_";
6667  ExtCatName += OCD->getNameAsString();
6668 
6669  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6670  auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.CategorynfABITy);
6671  values.add(GetClassName(OCD->getIdentifier()->getName()));
6672  // meta-class entry symbol
6673  values.add(GetClassGlobal(Interface, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition));
6674  std::string listName =
6675  (Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString() + "_$_" + OCD->getName()).str();
6676 
6677  SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 16> instanceMethods;
6678  SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 8> classMethods;
6679  for (const auto *MD : OCD->methods()) {
6680  if (MD->isDirectMethod())
6681  continue;
6682  if (MD->isInstanceMethod()) {
6683  instanceMethods.push_back(MD);
6684  } else {
6685  classMethods.push_back(MD);
6686  }
6687  }
6688 
6689  auto instanceMethodList = emitMethodList(
6690  listName, MethodListType::CategoryInstanceMethods, instanceMethods);
6691  auto classMethodList = emitMethodList(
6692  listName, MethodListType::CategoryClassMethods, classMethods);
6693  values.add(instanceMethodList);
6694  values.add(classMethodList);
6695  // Keep track of whether we have actual metadata to emit.
6696  bool isEmptyCategory =
6697  instanceMethodList->isNullValue() && classMethodList->isNullValue();
6698 
6699  const ObjCCategoryDecl *Category =
6700  Interface->FindCategoryDeclaration(OCD->getIdentifier());
6701  if (Category) {
6702  SmallString<256> ExtName;
6703  llvm::raw_svector_ostream(ExtName)
6704  << Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString() << "_$_" << OCD->getName();
6705  auto protocolList =
6706  EmitProtocolList("_OBJC_CATEGORY_PROTOCOLS_$_" +
6707  Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString() + "_$_" +
6708  Category->getName(),
6709  Category->protocol_begin(), Category->protocol_end());
6710  auto propertyList = EmitPropertyList("_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + ExtName.str(),
6711  OCD, Category, ObjCTypes, false);
6712  auto classPropertyList =
6713  EmitPropertyList("_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + ExtName.str(), OCD,
6714  Category, ObjCTypes, true);
6715  values.add(protocolList);
6716  values.add(propertyList);
6717  values.add(classPropertyList);
6718  isEmptyCategory &= protocolList->isNullValue() &&
6719  propertyList->isNullValue() &&
6720  classPropertyList->isNullValue();
6721  } else {
6722  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
6723  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
6724  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
6725  }
6726 
6727  if (isEmptyCategory) {
6728  // Empty category, don't emit any metadata.
6729  values.abandon();
6730  MethodDefinitions.clear();
6731  return;
6732  }
6733 
6734  unsigned Size =
6735  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.CategorynfABITy);
6736  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6737 
6738  llvm::GlobalVariable *GCATV =
6739  finishAndCreateGlobal(values, ExtCatName.str(), CGM);
6740  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GCATV);
6741  if (Interface->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>())
6742  DefinedStubCategories.push_back(GCATV);
6743  else
6744  DefinedCategories.push_back(GCATV);
6745 
6746  // Determine if this category is also "non-lazy".
6747  if (ImplementationIsNonLazy(OCD))
6748  DefinedNonLazyCategories.push_back(GCATV);
6749  // method definition entries must be clear for next implementation.
6750  MethodDefinitions.clear();
6751 }
6752 
6753 /// emitMethodConstant - Return a struct objc_method constant. If
6754 /// forProtocol is true, the implementation will be null; otherwise,
6755 /// the method must have a definition registered with the runtime.
6756 ///
6757 /// struct _objc_method {
6758 /// SEL _cmd;
6759 /// char *method_type;
6760 /// char *_imp;
6761 /// }
6762 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::emitMethodConstant(ConstantArrayBuilder &builder,
6763  const ObjCMethodDecl *MD,
6764  bool forProtocol) {
6765  auto method = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
6766  method.addBitCast(GetMethodVarName(MD->getSelector()),
6767  ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
6768  method.add(GetMethodVarType(MD));
6769 
6770  if (forProtocol) {
6771  // Protocol methods have no implementation. So, this entry is always NULL.
6772  method.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6773  } else {
6774  llvm::Function *fn = GetMethodDefinition(MD);
6775  assert(fn && "no definition for method?");
6776  method.addBitCast(fn, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6777  }
6778 
6779  method.finishAndAddTo(builder);
6780 }
6781 
6782 /// Build meta-data for method declarations.
6783 ///
6784 /// struct _method_list_t {
6785 /// uint32_t entsize; // sizeof(struct _objc_method)
6786 /// uint32_t method_count;
6787 /// struct _objc_method method_list[method_count];
6788 /// }
6789 ///
6790 llvm::Constant *
6791 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::emitMethodList(Twine name, MethodListType kind,
6792  ArrayRef<const ObjCMethodDecl *> methods) {
6793  // Return null for empty list.
6794  if (methods.empty())
6795  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.MethodListnfABIPtrTy);
6796 
6797  StringRef prefix;
6798  bool forProtocol;
6799  switch (kind) {
6800  case MethodListType::CategoryInstanceMethods:
6801  prefix = "_OBJC_$_CATEGORY_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
6802  forProtocol = false;
6803  break;
6804  case MethodListType::CategoryClassMethods:
6805  prefix = "_OBJC_$_CATEGORY_CLASS_METHODS_";
6806  forProtocol = false;
6807  break;
6808  case MethodListType::InstanceMethods:
6809  prefix = "_OBJC_$_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
6810  forProtocol = false;
6811  break;
6812  case MethodListType::ClassMethods:
6813  prefix = "_OBJC_$_CLASS_METHODS_";
6814  forProtocol = false;
6815  break;
6816 
6817  case MethodListType::ProtocolInstanceMethods:
6818  prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
6819  forProtocol = true;
6820  break;
6821  case MethodListType::ProtocolClassMethods:
6822  prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_CLASS_METHODS_";
6823  forProtocol = true;
6824  break;
6825  case MethodListType::OptionalProtocolInstanceMethods:
6826  prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_INSTANCE_METHODS_OPT_";
6827  forProtocol = true;
6828  break;
6829  case MethodListType::OptionalProtocolClassMethods:
6830  prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_CLASS_METHODS_OPT_";
6831  forProtocol = true;
6832  break;
6833  }
6834 
6835  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6836  auto values = builder.beginStruct();
6837 
6838  // sizeof(struct _objc_method)
6839  unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
6840  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6841  // method_count
6842  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, methods.size());
6843  auto methodArray = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
6844  for (auto MD : methods)
6845  emitMethodConstant(methodArray, MD, forProtocol);
6846  methodArray.finishAndAddTo(values);
6847 
6848  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = finishAndCreateGlobal(values, prefix + name, CGM);
6849  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
6850  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.MethodListnfABIPtrTy);
6851 }
6852 
6853 /// ObjCIvarOffsetVariable - Returns the ivar offset variable for
6854 /// the given ivar.
6855 llvm::GlobalVariable *
6856 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
6857  const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar) {
6858  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Container = Ivar->getContainingInterface();
6859  llvm::SmallString<64> Name("OBJC_IVAR_$_");
6860  Name += Container->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6861  Name += ".";
6862  Name += Ivar->getName();
6863  llvm::GlobalVariable *IvarOffsetGV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name);
6864  if (!IvarOffsetGV) {
6865  IvarOffsetGV =
6866  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy,
6867  false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
6868  nullptr, Name.str());
6869  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
6870  bool IsPrivateOrPackage =
6871  Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Private ||
6872  Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Package;
6873 
6874  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ContainingID = Ivar->getContainingInterface();
6875 
6876  if (ContainingID->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6877  IvarOffsetGV
6878  ->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
6879  else if (ContainingID->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() && !IsPrivateOrPackage)
6880  IvarOffsetGV
6881  ->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
6882  }
6883  }
6884  return IvarOffsetGV;
6885 }
6886 
6887 llvm::Constant *
6888 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarOffsetVar(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
6889  const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar,
6890  unsigned long int Offset) {
6891  llvm::GlobalVariable *IvarOffsetGV = ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(ID, Ivar);
6892  IvarOffsetGV->setInitializer(
6893  llvm::ConstantInt::get(ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy, Offset));
6894  IvarOffsetGV->setAlignment(llvm::Align(
6895  CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy)));
6896 
6897  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
6898  // FIXME: This matches gcc, but shouldn't the visibility be set on the use
6899  // as well (i.e., in ObjCIvarOffsetVariable).
6900  if (Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Private ||
6901  Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Package ||
6902  ID->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
6903  IvarOffsetGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6904  else
6905  IvarOffsetGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
6906  }
6907 
6908  // If ID's layout is known, then make the global constant. This serves as a
6909  // useful assertion: we'll never use this variable to calculate ivar offsets,
6910  // so if the runtime tries to patch it then we should crash.
6911  if (isClassLayoutKnownStatically(ID))
6912  IvarOffsetGV->setConstant(true);
6913 
6914  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6915  IvarOffsetGV->setSection("__DATA, __objc_ivar");
6916  return IvarOffsetGV;
6917 }
6918 
6919 /// EmitIvarList - Emit the ivar list for the given
6920 /// implementation. The return value has type
6921 /// IvarListnfABIPtrTy.
6922 /// struct _ivar_t {
6923 /// unsigned [long] int *offset; // pointer to ivar offset location
6924 /// char *name;
6925 /// char *type;
6926 /// uint32_t alignment;
6927 /// uint32_t size;
6928 /// }
6929 /// struct _ivar_list_t {
6930 /// uint32 entsize; // sizeof(struct _ivar_t)
6931 /// uint32 count;
6932 /// struct _iver_t list[count];
6933 /// }
6934 ///
6935 
6936 llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarList(
6937  const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
6938 
6939  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6940  auto ivarList = builder.beginStruct();
6941  ivarList.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy,
6942  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.IvarnfABITy));
6943  auto ivarCountSlot = ivarList.addPlaceholder();
6944  auto ivars = ivarList.beginArray(ObjCTypes.IvarnfABITy);
6945 
6946  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = ID->getClassInterface();
6947  assert(OID && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarList - null interface");
6948 
6949  // FIXME. Consolidate this with similar code in GenerateClass.
6950 
6951  for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = OID->all_declared_ivar_begin();
6952  IVD; IVD = IVD->getNextIvar()) {
6953  // Ignore unnamed bit-fields.
6954  if (!IVD->getDeclName())
6955  continue;
6956 
6957  auto ivar = ivars.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.IvarnfABITy);
6958  ivar.add(EmitIvarOffsetVar(ID->getClassInterface(), IVD,
6959  ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, ID, IVD)));
6960  ivar.add(GetMethodVarName(IVD->getIdentifier()));
6961  ivar.add(GetMethodVarType(IVD));
6962  llvm::Type *FieldTy =
6963  CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(IVD->getType());
6964  unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(FieldTy);
6965  unsigned Align = CGM.getContext().getPreferredTypeAlign(
6966  IVD->getType().getTypePtr()) >> 3;
6967  Align = llvm::Log2_32(Align);
6968  ivar.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Align);
6969  // NOTE. Size of a bitfield does not match gcc's, because of the
6970  // way bitfields are treated special in each. But I am told that
6971  // 'size' for bitfield ivars is ignored by the runtime so it does
6972  // not matter. If it matters, there is enough info to get the
6973  // bitfield right!
6974  ivar.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6975  ivar.finishAndAddTo(ivars);
6976  }
6977  // Return null for empty list.
6978  if (ivars.empty()) {
6979  ivars.abandon();
6980  ivarList.abandon();
6981  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.IvarListnfABIPtrTy);
6982  }
6983 
6984  auto ivarCount = ivars.size();
6985  ivars.finishAndAddTo(ivarList);
6986  ivarList.fillPlaceholderWithInt(ivarCountSlot, ObjCTypes.IntTy, ivarCount);
6987 
6988  const char *Prefix = "_OBJC_$_INSTANCE_VARIABLES_";
6989  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = finishAndCreateGlobal(
6990  ivarList, Prefix + OID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(), CGM);
6991  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
6992  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.IvarListnfABIPtrTy);
6993 }
6994 
6995 llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetOrEmitProtocolRef(
6996  const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
6997  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()];
6998 
6999  assert(!PD->isNonRuntimeProtocol() &&
7000  "attempting to GetOrEmit a non-runtime protocol");
7001  if (!Entry) {
7002  // We use the initializer as a marker of whether this is a forward
7003  // reference or not. At module finalization we add the empty
7004  // contents for protocols which were referenced but never defined.
7005  llvm::SmallString<64> Protocol;
7006  llvm::raw_svector_ostream(Protocol) << "_OBJC_PROTOCOL_$_"
7007  << PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7008 
7009  Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABITy,
7010  false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
7011  nullptr, Protocol);
7012  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
7013  Entry->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(Protocol));
7014  }
7015 
7016  return Entry;
7017 }
7018 
7019 /// GetOrEmitProtocol - Generate the protocol meta-data:
7020 /// @code
7021 /// struct _protocol_t {
7022 /// id isa; // NULL
7023 /// const char * const protocol_name;
7024 /// const struct _protocol_list_t * protocol_list; // super protocols
7025 /// const struct method_list_t * const instance_methods;
7026 /// const struct method_list_t * const class_methods;
7027 /// const struct method_list_t *optionalInstanceMethods;
7028 /// const struct method_list_t *optionalClassMethods;
7029 /// const struct _prop_list_t * properties;
7030 /// const uint32_t size; // sizeof(struct _protocol_t)
7031 /// const uint32_t flags; // = 0
7032 /// const char ** extendedMethodTypes;
7033 /// const char *demangledName;
7034 /// const struct _prop_list_t * class_properties;
7035 /// }
7036 /// @endcode
7037 ///
7038 
7039 llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetOrEmitProtocol(
7040  const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
7041  llvm::GlobalVariable *Entry = Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()];
7042 
7043  // Early exit if a defining object has already been generated.
7044  if (Entry && Entry->hasInitializer())
7045  return Entry;
7046 
7047  // Use the protocol definition, if there is one.
7048  assert(PD->hasDefinition() &&
7049  "emitting protocol metadata without definition");
7050  PD = PD->getDefinition();
7051 
7052  auto methodLists = ProtocolMethodLists::get(PD);
7053 
7054  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7055  auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABITy);
7056 
7057  // isa is NULL
7058  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7059  values.add(GetClassName(PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
7060  values.add(EmitProtocolList("_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_REFS_"
7061  + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
7062  PD->protocol_begin(),
7063  PD->protocol_end()));
7064  values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
7065  ProtocolMethodLists::RequiredInstanceMethods));
7066  values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
7067  ProtocolMethodLists::RequiredClassMethods));
7068  values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
7069  ProtocolMethodLists::OptionalInstanceMethods));
7070  values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
7071  ProtocolMethodLists::OptionalClassMethods));
7072  values.add(EmitPropertyList(
7073  "_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
7074  nullptr, PD, ObjCTypes, false));
7075  uint32_t Size =
7076  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABITy);
7077  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
7078  values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, 0);
7079  values.add(EmitProtocolMethodTypes("_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_METHOD_TYPES_"
7080  + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
7081  methodLists.emitExtendedTypesArray(this),
7082  ObjCTypes));
7083 
7084  // const char *demangledName;
7085  values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7086 
7087  values.add(EmitPropertyList(
7088  "_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
7089  nullptr, PD, ObjCTypes, true));
7090 
7091  if (Entry) {
7092  // Already created, fix the linkage and update the initializer.
7093  Entry->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
7094  values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(Entry);
7095  } else {
7096  llvm::SmallString<64> symbolName;
7097  llvm::raw_svector_ostream(symbolName)
7098  << "_OBJC_PROTOCOL_$_" << PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7099 
7100  Entry = values.finishAndCreateGlobal(symbolName, CGM.getPointerAlign(),
7101  /*constant*/ false,
7102  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
7103  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
7104  Entry->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(symbolName));
7105 
7106  Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()] = Entry;
7107  }
7108  Entry->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7109  CGM.addUsedGlobal(Entry);
7110 
7111  // Use this protocol meta-data to build protocol list table in section
7112  // __DATA, __objc_protolist
7113  llvm::SmallString<64> ProtocolRef;
7114  llvm::raw_svector_ostream(ProtocolRef) << "_OBJC_LABEL_PROTOCOL_$_"
7115  << PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7116 
7117  llvm::GlobalVariable *PTGV =
7118  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy,
7119  false, llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, Entry,
7120  ProtocolRef);
7121  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
7122  PTGV->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ProtocolRef));
7123  PTGV->setAlignment(llvm::Align(
7124  CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy)));
7125  PTGV->setSection(GetSectionName("__objc_protolist",
7126  "coalesced,no_dead_strip"));
7127  PTGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7128  CGM.addUsedGlobal(PTGV);
7129  return Entry;
7130 }
7131 
7132 /// EmitProtocolList - Generate protocol list meta-data:
7133 /// @code
7134 /// struct _protocol_list_t {
7135 /// long protocol_count; // Note, this is 32/64 bit
7136 /// struct _protocol_t[protocol_count];
7137 /// }
7138 /// @endcode
7139 ///
7140 llvm::Constant *
7141 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitProtocolList(Twine Name,
7142  ObjCProtocolDecl::protocol_iterator begin,
7143  ObjCProtocolDecl::protocol_iterator end) {
7144  // Just return null for empty protocol lists
7145  auto Protocols = GetRuntimeProtocolList(begin, end);
7146  if (Protocols.empty())
7147  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7148 
7149  SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 16> ProtocolRefs;
7150  ProtocolRefs.reserve(Protocols.size());
7151 
7152  for (const auto *PD : Protocols)
7153  ProtocolRefs.push_back(GetProtocolRef(PD));
7154 
7155  // If all of the protocols in the protocol list are objc_non_runtime_protocol
7156  // just return null
7157  if (ProtocolRefs.size() == 0)
7158  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7159 
7160  // FIXME: We shouldn't need to do this lookup here, should we?
7161  SmallString<256> TmpName;
7162  Name.toVector(TmpName);
7163  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
7164  CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(TmpName.str(), true);
7165  if (GV)
7166  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7167 
7168  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7169  auto values = builder.beginStruct();
7170  auto countSlot = values.addPlaceholder();
7171 
7172  // A null-terminated array of protocols.
7173  auto array = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy);
7174  for (auto const &proto : ProtocolRefs)
7175  array.add(proto);
7176  auto count = array.size();
7177  array.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy);
7178 
7179  array.finishAndAddTo(values);
7180  values.fillPlaceholderWithInt(countSlot, ObjCTypes.LongTy, count);
7181 
7182  GV = finishAndCreateGlobal(values, Name, CGM);
7183  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
7184  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV,
7185  ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7186 }
7187 
7188 /// EmitObjCValueForIvar - Code Gen for nonfragile ivar reference.
7189 /// This code gen. amounts to generating code for:
7190 /// @code
7191 /// (type *)((char *)base + _OBJC_IVAR_$_.ivar;
7192 /// @encode
7193 ///
7194 LValue CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCValueForIvar(
7195  CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7196  QualType ObjectTy,
7197  llvm::Value *BaseValue,
7198  const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar,
7199  unsigned CVRQualifiers) {
7200  ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = ObjectTy->castAs<ObjCObjectType>()->getInterface();
7201  llvm::Value *Offset = EmitIvarOffset(CGF, ID, Ivar);
7202  return EmitValueForIvarAtOffset(CGF, ID, BaseValue, Ivar, CVRQualifiers,
7203  Offset);
7204 }
7205 
7206 llvm::Value *
7207 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarOffset(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7208  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface,
7209  const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar) {
7210  llvm::Value *IvarOffsetValue;
7211  if (isClassLayoutKnownStatically(Interface)) {
7212  IvarOffsetValue = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
7213  ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy,
7214  ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, Interface->getImplementation(), Ivar));
7215  } else {
7216  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(Interface, Ivar);
7217  IvarOffsetValue =
7218  CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(GV->getValueType(), GV,
7219  CGF.getSizeAlign(), "ivar");
7220  if (IsIvarOffsetKnownIdempotent(CGF, Ivar))
7221  cast<llvm::LoadInst>(IvarOffsetValue)
7222  ->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("invariant.load"),
7223  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, None));
7224  }
7225 
7226  // This could be 32bit int or 64bit integer depending on the architecture.
7227  // Cast it to 64bit integer value, if it is a 32bit integer ivar offset value
7228  // as this is what caller always expects.
7229  if (ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy == ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7230  IvarOffsetValue = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7231  IvarOffsetValue, ObjCTypes.LongTy, true, "ivar.conv");
7232  return IvarOffsetValue;
7233 }
7234 
7235 static void appendSelectorForMessageRefTable(std::string &buffer,
7236  Selector selector) {
7237  if (selector.isUnarySelector()) {
7238  buffer += selector.getNameForSlot(0);
7239  return;
7240  }
7241 
7242  for (unsigned i = 0, e = selector.getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i) {
7243  buffer += selector.getNameForSlot(i);
7244  buffer += '_';
7245  }
7246 }
7247 
7248 /// Emit a "vtable" message send. We emit a weak hidden-visibility
7249 /// struct, initially containing the selector pointer and a pointer to
7250 /// a "fixup" variant of the appropriate objc_msgSend. To call, we
7251 /// load and call the function pointer, passing the address of the
7252 /// struct as the second parameter. The runtime determines whether
7253 /// the selector is currently emitted using vtable dispatch; if so, it
7254 /// substitutes a stub function which simply tail-calls through the
7255 /// appropriate vtable slot, and if not, it substitues a stub function
7256 /// which tail-calls objc_msgSend. Both stubs adjust the selector
7257 /// argument to correctly point to the selector.
7258 RValue
7259 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitVTableMessageSend(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7260  ReturnValueSlot returnSlot,
7261  QualType resultType,
7262  Selector selector,
7263  llvm::Value *arg0,
7264  QualType arg0Type,
7265  bool isSuper,
7266  const CallArgList &formalArgs,
7267  const ObjCMethodDecl *method) {
7268  // Compute the actual arguments.
7269  CallArgList args;
7270 
7271  // First argument: the receiver / super-call structure.
7272  if (!isSuper)
7273  arg0 = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(arg0, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7274  args.add(RValue::get(arg0), arg0Type);
7275 
7276  // Second argument: a pointer to the message ref structure. Leave
7277  // the actual argument value blank for now.
7278  args.add(RValue::get(nullptr), ObjCTypes.MessageRefCPtrTy);
7279 
7280  args.insert(args.end(), formalArgs.begin(), formalArgs.end());
7281 
7282  MessageSendInfo MSI = getMessageSendInfo(method, resultType, args);
7283 
7284  NullReturnState nullReturn;
7285 
7286  // Find the function to call and the mangled name for the message
7287  // ref structure. Using a different mangled name wouldn't actually
7288  // be a problem; it would just be a waste.
7289  //
7290  // The runtime currently never uses vtable dispatch for anything
7291  // except normal, non-super message-sends.
7292  // FIXME: don't use this for that.
7293  llvm::FunctionCallee fn = nullptr;
7294  std::string messageRefName("_");
7295  if (CGM.ReturnSlotInterferesWithArgs(MSI.CallInfo)) {
7296  if (isSuper) {
7297  fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendSuper2StretFixupFn();
7298  messageRefName += "objc_msgSendSuper2_stret_fixup";
7299  } else {
7300  nullReturn.init(CGF, arg0);
7301  fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendStretFixupFn();
7302  messageRefName += "objc_msgSend_stret_fixup";
7303  }
7304  } else if (!isSuper && CGM.ReturnTypeUsesFPRet(resultType)) {
7305  fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendFpretFixupFn();
7306  messageRefName += "objc_msgSend_fpret_fixup";
7307  } else {
7308  if (isSuper) {
7309  fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendSuper2FixupFn();
7310  messageRefName += "objc_msgSendSuper2_fixup";
7311  } else {
7312  fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendFixupFn();
7313  messageRefName += "objc_msgSend_fixup";
7314  }
7315  }
7316  assert(fn && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitMessageSend");
7317  messageRefName += '_';
7318 
7319  // Append the selector name, except use underscores anywhere we
7320  // would have used colons.
7321  appendSelectorForMessageRefTable(messageRefName, selector);
7322 
7323  llvm::GlobalVariable *messageRef
7324  = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(messageRefName);
7325  if (!messageRef) {
7326  // Build the message ref structure.
7327  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7328  auto values = builder.beginStruct();
7329  values.add(cast<llvm::Constant>(fn.getCallee()));
7330  values.add(GetMethodVarName(selector));
7331  messageRef = values.finishAndCreateGlobal(messageRefName,
7332  CharUnits::fromQuantity(16),
7333  /*constant*/ false,
7334  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
7335  messageRef->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7336  messageRef->setSection(GetSectionName("__objc_msgrefs", "coalesced"));
7337  }
7338 
7339  bool requiresnullCheck = false;
7340  if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && method)
7341  for (const auto *ParamDecl : method->parameters()) {
7342  if (ParamDecl->isDestroyedInCallee()) {
7343  if (!nullReturn.NullBB)
7344  nullReturn.init(CGF, arg0);
7345  requiresnullCheck = true;
7346  break;
7347  }
7348  }
7349 
7350  Address mref =
7351  Address(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(messageRef, ObjCTypes.MessageRefPtrTy),
7352  ObjCTypes.MessageRefTy, CGF.getPointerAlign());
7353 
7354  // Update the message ref argument.
7355  args[1].setRValue(RValue::get(mref.getPointer()));
7356 
7357  // Load the function to call from the message ref table.
7358  Address calleeAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(mref, 0);
7359  llvm::Value *calleePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(calleeAddr, "msgSend_fn");
7360 
7361  calleePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(calleePtr, MSI.MessengerType);
7362  CGCallee callee(CGCalleeInfo(), calleePtr);
7363 
7364  RValue result = CGF.EmitCall(MSI.CallInfo, callee, returnSlot, args);
7365  return nullReturn.complete(CGF, returnSlot, result, resultType, formalArgs,
7366  requiresnullCheck ? method : nullptr);
7367 }
7368 
7369 /// Generate code for a message send expression in the nonfragile abi.
7370 CodeGen::RValue
7371 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateMessageSend(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7372  ReturnValueSlot Return,
7373  QualType ResultType,
7374  Selector Sel,
7375  llvm::Value *Receiver,
7376  const CallArgList &CallArgs,
7377  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
7378  const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
7379  return isVTableDispatchedSelector(Sel)
7380  ? EmitVTableMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType, Sel,
7381  Receiver, CGF.getContext().getObjCIdType(),
7382  false, CallArgs, Method)
7383  : EmitMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType, Sel,
7384  Receiver, CGF.getContext().getObjCIdType(),
7385  false, CallArgs, Method, Class, ObjCTypes);
7386 }
7387 
7388 llvm::Constant *
7389 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassGlobal(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7390  bool metaclass,
7391  ForDefinition_t isForDefinition) {
7392  auto prefix =
7393  (metaclass ? getMetaclassSymbolPrefix() : getClassSymbolPrefix());
7394  return GetClassGlobal((prefix + ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()).str(),
7395  isForDefinition,
7396  ID->isWeakImported(),
7397  !isForDefinition
7398  && CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()
7399  && ID->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>());
7400 }
7401 
7402 llvm::Constant *
7403 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassGlobal(StringRef Name,
7404  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition,
7405  bool Weak, bool DLLImport) {
7406  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes L =
7407  Weak ? llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage
7408  : llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage;
7409 
7410  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name);
7411  if (!GV || GV->getValueType() != ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy) {
7412  auto *NewGV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy, false, L,
7413  nullptr, Name);
7414 
7415  if (DLLImport)
7416  NewGV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
7417 
7418  if (GV) {
7419  GV->replaceAllUsesWith(
7420  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NewGV, GV->getType()));
7421  GV->eraseFromParent();
7422  }
7423  GV = NewGV;
7424  CGM.getModule().getGlobalList().push_back(GV);
7425  }
7426 
7427  assert(GV->getLinkage() == L);
7428  return GV;
7429 }
7430 
7431 llvm::Constant *
7432 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassGlobalForClassRef(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7433  llvm::Constant *ClassGV = GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ false,
7434  NotForDefinition);
7435 
7436  if (!ID->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>())
7437  return ClassGV;
7438 
7439  ClassGV = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(ClassGV, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7440 
7441  // Stub classes are pointer-aligned. Classrefs pointing at stub classes
7442  // must set the least significant bit set to 1.
7443  auto *Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 1);
7444  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(CGM.Int8Ty, ClassGV, Idx);
7445 }
7446 
7447 llvm::Value *
7448 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitLoadOfClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7449  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7450  llvm::GlobalVariable *Entry) {
7451  if (ID && ID->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>()) {
7452  // Classrefs pointing at Objective-C stub classes must be loaded by calling
7453  // a special runtime function.
7454  return CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
7455  ObjCTypes.getLoadClassrefFn(), Entry, "load_classref_result");
7456  }
7457 
7458  CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
7459  return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Entry->getValueType(), Entry, Align);
7460 }
7461 
7462 llvm::Value *
7463 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitClassRefFromId(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7464  IdentifierInfo *II,
7465  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7466  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = ClassReferences[II];
7467 
7468  if (!Entry) {
7469  llvm::Constant *ClassGV;
7470  if (ID) {
7471  ClassGV = GetClassGlobalForClassRef(ID);
7472  } else {
7473  ClassGV = GetClassGlobal((getClassSymbolPrefix() + II->getName()).str(),
7474  NotForDefinition);
7475  assert(ClassGV->getType() == ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy &&
7476  "classref was emitted with the wrong type?");
7477  }
7478 
7479  std::string SectionName =
7480  GetSectionName("__objc_classrefs", "regular,no_dead_strip");
7481  Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7482  CGM.getModule(), ClassGV->getType(), false,
7483  getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName), ClassGV,
7484  "OBJC_CLASSLIST_REFERENCES_$_");
7485  Entry->setAlignment(CGF.getPointerAlign().getAsAlign());
7486  if (!ID || !ID->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>())
7487  Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7488 
7489  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7490  }
7491 
7492  return EmitLoadOfClassRef(CGF, ID, Entry);
7493 }
7494 
7495 llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7496  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7497  // If the class has the objc_runtime_visible attribute, we need to
7498  // use the Objective-C runtime to get the class.
7499  if (ID->hasAttr<ObjCRuntimeVisibleAttr>())
7500  return EmitClassRefViaRuntime(CGF, ID, ObjCTypes);
7501 
7502  return EmitClassRefFromId(CGF, ID->getIdentifier(), ID);
7503 }
7504 
7505 llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitNSAutoreleasePoolClassRef(
7506  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
7507  IdentifierInfo *II = &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("NSAutoreleasePool");
7508  return EmitClassRefFromId(CGF, II, nullptr);
7509 }

7511 llvm::Value *
7512 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSuperClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7513  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7514  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = SuperClassReferences[ID->getIdentifier()];
7515 
7516  if (!Entry) {
7517  llvm::Constant *ClassGV = GetClassGlobalForClassRef(ID);
7518  std::string SectionName =
7519  GetSectionName("__objc_superrefs", "regular,no_dead_strip");
7520  Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ClassGV->getType(), false,
7521  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, ClassGV,
7522  "OBJC_CLASSLIST_SUP_REFS_$_");
7523  Entry->setAlignment(CGF.getPointerAlign().getAsAlign());
7524  Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7525  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7526  }
7527 
7528  return EmitLoadOfClassRef(CGF, ID, Entry);
7529 }

7531 /// EmitMetaClassRef - Return a Value * of the address of _class_t
7532 /// meta-data
7533 ///
7534 llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitMetaClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7535  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7536  bool Weak) {
7537  CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
7538  llvm::GlobalVariable * &Entry = MetaClassReferences[ID->getIdentifier()];
7539  if (!Entry) {
7540  auto MetaClassGV = GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
7541  std::string SectionName =
7542  GetSectionName("__objc_superrefs", "regular,no_dead_strip");
7543  Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy,
7544  false, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
7545  MetaClassGV, "OBJC_CLASSLIST_SUP_REFS_$_");
7546  Entry->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
7547  Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7548  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7549  }
7550 
7551  return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy, Entry, Align);
7552 }

7554 /// GetClass - Return a reference to the class for the given interface
7555 /// decl.
7556 llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClass(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7557  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7558  if (ID->isWeakImported()) {
7559  auto ClassGV = GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition);
7560  (void)ClassGV;
7561  assert(!isa<llvm::GlobalVariable>(ClassGV) ||
7562  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(ClassGV)->hasExternalWeakLinkage());
7563  }
7564 
7565  return EmitClassRef(CGF, ID);
7566 }
7567 
7568 /// Generates a message send where the super is the receiver. This is
7569 /// a message send to self with special delivery semantics indicating
7570 /// which class's method should be called.
7571 CodeGen::RValue
7572 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateMessageSendSuper(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7573  ReturnValueSlot Return,
7574  QualType ResultType,
7575  Selector Sel,
7576  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
7577  bool isCategoryImpl,
7578  llvm::Value *Receiver,
7579  bool IsClassMessage,
7580  const CodeGen::CallArgList &CallArgs,
7581  const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
7582  // ...
7583  // Create and init a super structure; this is a (receiver, class)
7584  // pair we will pass to objc_msgSendSuper.
7585  Address ObjCSuper =
7586  CGF.CreateTempAlloca(ObjCTypes.SuperTy, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
7587  "objc_super");
7588 
7589  llvm::Value *ReceiverAsObject =
7590  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Receiver, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7591  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(ReceiverAsObject,
7592  CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 0));
7593 
7594  // If this is a class message the metaclass is passed as the target.
7595  llvm::Value *Target;
7596  if (IsClassMessage)
7597  Target = EmitMetaClassRef(CGF, Class, Class->isWeakImported());
7598  else
7599  Target = EmitSuperClassRef(CGF, Class);
7600 
7601  // FIXME: We shouldn't need to do this cast, rectify the ASTContext and
7602  // ObjCTypes types.
7603  llvm::Type *ClassTy =
7604  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getObjCClassType());
7605  Target = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Target, ClassTy);
7606  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Target, CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 1));
7607 
7608  return (isVTableDispatchedSelector(Sel))
7609  ? EmitVTableMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType, Sel,
7610  ObjCSuper.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.SuperPtrCTy,
7611  true, CallArgs, Method)
7612  : EmitMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType, Sel,
7613  ObjCSuper.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.SuperPtrCTy,
7614  true, CallArgs, Method, Class, ObjCTypes);
7615 }
7616 
7617 llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSelector(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7618  Selector Sel) {
7619  Address Addr = EmitSelectorAddr(Sel);
7620 
7621  llvm::LoadInst* LI = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
7622  LI->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("invariant.load"),
7623  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, None));
7624  return LI;
7625 }
7626 
7627 Address CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSelectorAddr(Selector Sel) {
7628  llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = SelectorReferences[Sel];
7629  CharUnits Align = CGM.getPointerAlign();
7630  if (!Entry) {
7631  llvm::Constant *Casted =
7632  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GetMethodVarName(Sel),
7633  ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
7634  std::string SectionName =
7635  GetSectionName("__objc_selrefs", "literal_pointers,no_dead_strip");
7636  Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7637  CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy, false,
7638  getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName), Casted,
7639  "OBJC_SELECTOR_REFERENCES_");
7640  Entry->setExternallyInitialized(true);
7641  Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7642  Entry->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
7643  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7644  }
7645 
7646  return Address(Entry, ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy, Align);
7647 }
