7649 /// EmitObjCIvarAssign - Code gen for assigning to a __strong object.
7650 /// objc_assign_ivar (id src, id *dst, ptrdiff_t)
7651 ///
7652 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCIvarAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7653  llvm::Value *src,
7654  Address dst,
7655  llvm::Value *ivarOffset) {
7656  llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
7657  if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
7658  unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
7659  assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
7660  src = (Size == 4 ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7661  : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7662  src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7663  }
7664  src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7665  llvm::Value *dstVal =
7666  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
7667  llvm::Value *args[] = {src, dstVal, ivarOffset};
7668  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignIvarFn(), args);
7669 }

7672 /// objc_assign_strongCast (id src, id *dst)
7673 ///
7674 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCStrongCastAssign(
7675  CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,

7678  if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
7679  unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
7680  assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
7681  src = (Size == 4 ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7682  : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7683  src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7684  }
7685  src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7686  llvm::Value *dstVal =
7687  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
7688  llvm::Value *args[] = {src, dstVal};
7689  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignStrongCastFn(),
7690  args, "weakassign");
7691 }

7693 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitGCMemmoveCollectable(
7694  CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7695  Address DestPtr,
7696  Address SrcPtr,
7697  llvm::Value *Size) {
7698  SrcPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(SrcPtr, CGF.Int8Ty);
7699  DestPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(DestPtr, CGF.Int8Ty);
7700  llvm::Value *args[] = { DestPtr.getPointer(), SrcPtr.getPointer(), Size };
7701  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.GcMemmoveCollectableFn(), args);
7702 }

7704 /// EmitObjCWeakRead - Code gen for loading value of a __weak
7705 /// object: objc_read_weak (id *src)
7706 ///
7707 llvm::Value * CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCWeakRead(
7708  CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7709  Address AddrWeakObj) {
7710  llvm::Type *DestTy = AddrWeakObj.getElementType();
7711  llvm::Value *AddrWeakObjVal = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(
7712  AddrWeakObj.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
7713  llvm::Value *read_weak =
7714  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcReadWeakFn(),
7715  AddrWeakObjVal, "weakread");
7716  read_weak = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(read_weak, DestTy);
7717  return read_weak;

7723 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCWeakAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,

7730  : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7731  src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7732  }

7741 /// EmitObjCGlobalAssign - Code gen for assigning to a __strong object.
7742 /// objc_assign_global (id src, id *dst)
7743 ///
7744 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCGlobalAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7745  llvm::Value *src, Address dst,
7746  bool threadlocal) {
7747  llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
7748  if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
7749  unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
7750  assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
7751  src = (Size == 4 ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7752  : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7753  src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7754  }
7755  src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7756  llvm::Value *dstVal =
7757  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
7758  llvm::Value *args[] = {src, dstVal};
7759  if (!threadlocal)
7760  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignGlobalFn(),
7761  args, "globalassign");
7762  else
7763  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignThreadLocalFn(),
7764  args, "threadlocalassign");
7765 }
7766 
7767 void
7768 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSynchronizedStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7769  const ObjCAtSynchronizedStmt &S) {
7770  EmitAtSynchronizedStmt(CGF, S, ObjCTypes.getSyncEnterFn(),
7771  ObjCTypes.getSyncExitFn());
7772 }
7773 
7774 llvm::Constant *
7775 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetEHType(QualType T) {
7776  // There's a particular fixed type info for 'id'.
7777  if (T->isObjCIdType() || T->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
7778  auto *IDEHType = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable("OBJC_EHTYPE_id");
7779  if (!IDEHType) {
7780  IDEHType =
7781  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.EHTypeTy, false,
7782  llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
7783  "OBJC_EHTYPE_id");
7784  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
7785  IDEHType->setDLLStorageClass(getStorage(CGM, "OBJC_EHTYPE_id"));
7786  }
7787  return IDEHType;
7788  }
7789 
7790  // All other types should be Objective-C interface pointer types.
7791  const ObjCObjectPointerType *PT = T->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
7792  assert(PT && "Invalid @catch type.");
7793 
7794  const ObjCInterfaceType *IT = PT->getInterfaceType();
7795  assert(IT && "Invalid @catch type.");
7796 
7797  return GetInterfaceEHType(IT->getDecl(), NotForDefinition);
7798 }
7799 
7800 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitTryStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7801  const ObjCAtTryStmt &S) {
7802  EmitTryCatchStmt(CGF, S, ObjCTypes.getObjCBeginCatchFn(),
7803  ObjCTypes.getObjCEndCatchFn(),
7804  ObjCTypes.getExceptionRethrowFn());
7805 }
7806 
7807 /// EmitThrowStmt - Generate code for a throw statement.
7808 void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitThrowStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7809  const ObjCAtThrowStmt &S,
7810  bool ClearInsertionPoint) {
7811  if (const Expr *ThrowExpr = S.getThrowExpr()) {
7812  llvm::Value *Exception = CGF.EmitObjCThrowOperand(ThrowExpr);
7813  Exception = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Exception, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7814  llvm::CallBase *Call =
7815  CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(ObjCTypes.getExceptionThrowFn(), Exception);
7816  Call->setDoesNotReturn();
7817  } else {
7818  llvm::CallBase *Call =
7819  CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(ObjCTypes.getExceptionRethrowFn());
7820  Call->setDoesNotReturn();
7821  }
7822 
7823  CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
7824  if (ClearInsertionPoint)
7825  CGF.Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
7826 }
7827 
7828 llvm::Constant *
7829 CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetInterfaceEHType(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7830  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
7831  llvm::GlobalVariable * &Entry = EHTypeReferences[ID->getIdentifier()];
7832  StringRef ClassName = ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7833 
7834  // If we don't need a definition, return the entry if found or check
7835  // if we use an external reference.
7836  if (!IsForDefinition) {
7837  if (Entry)
7838  return Entry;
7839 
7840  // If this type (or a super class) has the __objc_exception__
7841  // attribute, emit an external reference.
7842  if (hasObjCExceptionAttribute(CGM.getContext(), ID)) {
7843  std::string EHTypeName = ("OBJC_EHTYPE_$_" + ClassName).str();
7844  Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.EHTypeTy,
7845  false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
7846  nullptr, EHTypeName);
7847  CGM.setGVProperties(Entry, ID);
7848  return Entry;
7849  }
7850  }
7851 
7852  // Otherwise we need to either make a new entry or fill in the initializer.
7853  assert((!Entry || !Entry->hasInitializer()) && "Duplicate EHType definition");
7854 
7855  std::string VTableName = "objc_ehtype_vtable";
7856  auto *VTableGV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(VTableName);
7857  if (!VTableGV) {
7858  VTableGV =
7859  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy, false,
7860  llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
7861  VTableName);
7862  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
7863  VTableGV->setDLLStorageClass(getStorage(CGM, VTableName));
7864  }
7865 
7866  llvm::Value *VTableIdx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 2);
7867  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7868  auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.EHTypeTy);
7869  values.add(
7870  llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(VTableGV->getValueType(),
7871  VTableGV, VTableIdx));
7872  values.add(GetClassName(ClassName));
7873  values.add(GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition));
7874 
7875  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes L = IsForDefinition
7876  ? llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage
7877  : llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage;
7878  if (Entry) {
7879  values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(Entry);
7880  Entry->setAlignment(CGM.getPointerAlign().getAsAlign());
7881  } else {
7882  Entry = values.finishAndCreateGlobal("OBJC_EHTYPE_$_" + ClassName,
7883  CGM.getPointerAlign(),
7884  /*constant*/ false,
7885  L);
7886  if (hasObjCExceptionAttribute(CGM.getContext(), ID))
7887  CGM.setGVProperties(Entry, ID);
7888  }
7889  assert(Entry->getLinkage() == L);
7890 
7891  if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
7892  if (ID->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
7893  Entry->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7894 
7895  if (IsForDefinition)
7896  if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
7897  Entry->setSection("__DATA,__objc_const");
7898 
7899  return Entry;
7900 }
7901 
7902 /* *** */
7903 
7904 CodeGen::CGObjCRuntime *
7905 CodeGen::CreateMacObjCRuntime(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) {
7906  switch (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.getKind()) {
7907  case ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX:
7908  return new CGObjCMac(CGM);
7909 
7910  case ObjCRuntime::MacOSX:
7911  case ObjCRuntime::iOS:
7912  case ObjCRuntime::WatchOS:
7913  return new CGObjCNonFragileABIMac(CGM);
7914 
7915  case ObjCRuntime::GNUstep:
7916  case ObjCRuntime::GCC:
7917  case ObjCRuntime::ObjFW:
7918  llvm_unreachable("these runtimes are not Mac runtimes");
7919  }
7920  llvm_unreachable("bad runtime");
7921 }
